article.headline: Cal State Northridge 67, UC Riverside 60
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Terrell Jones may have scored 18 points for Cal State Northridge in Saturday's Big West mens basketball game at UC Riverside, but it was his 11 rebounds which may have counted more in the Matadors 67-60 victory over the Highlanders. Playing at Riverside's Student Recreation Center, Jones teamed up with two others to grab double-digits in rebounds as the Matadors out-boarded the Highlanders 47-25 to win their first conference game of the season. Northridge improved to 1-2 in conference and 7-7 overall. Eight of Jones' boards came on the offensive glass, as the Matadors finished with 16 offensive rebounds and 19 second-chance points. Jones' was not the Matadors' only double-double on the night, as Jonathan Heard added 10 points and 10 rebounds. Thomas Shewmake added another 12 boards and eight points, while Rob Haynes drilled a few outside jumpers for another 10 Northridge points. A back-and-forth second half put Northridge in relative control with a 60-55 lead and less than two minutes left until the Highlanders' Justin Bell took a long rebound and turned it into a Chris Johnson fastbreak-layup. That cut Northridge's lead to only three with 1:21 remaining, but the visitors followed with what kept them in the game all-night long -- a Jones tip in -- and never looked back. Bell led Riverside with 17 points, four assists and three steals; and teammates Chris Johnson and Charles Jim-George added 15 and 12 points respectively as UCR dropped its 11th straight game to fall to 3-13, 0-4 in the Big West.
